==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pricksong
<hw>Prick"song`</hw> <pr>(?; 115)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Prick</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>, 4.]</ety> <def>Music written, or
noted, with dots or points; -- so called from the points or dots with
which it is noted down.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>He fights as you sing <qex>pricksong</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prickwood</ent>⟦br⟧
